<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 04 at 5:00AM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Randolph County
through 545 AM CDT...
At 459 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Budapest to 7 miles east of Mammoth
Spring. Movement was southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pocahontas...                     Reyno...
Maynard...                        Biggers...
O`Kean...                         Ravenden Springs...
Dalton...                         Attica...
Middlebrook...                    Ingram...
Shannon...                        Birdell...
Elnora...                         Elkins Park...
Brakebill...                      Warm Springs...
Hamil...                          Stokes...
Fender...                         Engelerg...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
